&lt;p&gt;    hey @jeking3, Github is only a mirror of the actual Apache repos which are located at &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. There is a requirement that the canonical source for Apache repos must reside on ASF controlled servers and that they be the authority for commits. We have all the available Github integrations enabled for our project, but the merge button is not an option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=thrift.git&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
